§ Result ⦉
<statement type='proposition'>
  ¶ ⦊
    ‖ The determinant of an invertible square real matrix is the
      multiplicative inverse of the determinant of the matrix. ⦉
  ⦉

  <proof>
    ¶ ⦊
      ‖ Let $A ∈ 𝗥^{n × n}$ be invertible. ⦉

      ‖ We want to show that
        ◇ ⦊
          ‖ \det (A^{-1}) = (det(A))^{-1}. ⦉
        ⦉⦉
    ⦉
  </proof>
</statement>